===message:I agree - good points.  We also have to remember that even the political parties (Whigs, Democratics, and the Know-Nothings) had secetional splits over slavery.  I feel disunion and war was certain to happen given the fact that events taken place (Kansas-Nebraska Act, Dred Scott decision, Lecompton constitution, Fugitive Slave Act of 1850 and the Compromise of 1850) only brought about more controversy and not amicable solutions. 
