===subject:Reply to Bowie
===from:Ursula Davis
===date:Sat Feb 15 15:00:08 2003
===message:I agreed with you up to the point of the difference in a fanatical leader or moderate.  I think that the difference would only be an issue of the time it took for succession and the Civil War.  Lincoln was somewhat of a moderate.  He wanted to stand firm on his party's ideals, but he still made sure not to be too strong in his comments.  For example, the statement he made about not agreeing with the tactics that John Brown used.  On the other hand, a fanatical leader would have fueled the fires more quickly by making statements the opposing side would have been offended by.  In either case, this would not have stopped the impending events.  
=========yorg=========
